                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="40997" author="ian" created="Thu, 21 Jun 2012 12:28:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As part of this effort need to ensure sanity-quota is updated to run tunefs.lustre -quota when USE_OFD is set and using a ldiskfs OSD.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="38958" author="liwei" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 21:18:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This depends on the basic Orion server support that will be introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1415&quot; title=&quot;lustre-client-tests on the client must be modified to support Orion servers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1415&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1415&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="38287" author="adilger" created="Tue, 8 May 2012 01:58:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Even if the default OST layer is not OFD, it is still useful to have the infrastructure to be able to test OFD on master in parallel with obdfilter.  This will ensure that the code in master continues to work after changes, and will simplify performance and functional comparisons of the two IO stacks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="30664" author="ian" created="Wed, 7 Mar 2012 21:24:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Due to quota enforcement not landing until later, delay this change&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
